	<h1>Resources</h1>
	<h3>Here are a few resources for where to learn more about climate change and of how to help:</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><a href="https://climate.nasa.gov/solutions/adaptation-mitigation/" target="_blank">nasa.gov</a></li>
		<li><a
				href="https://www.un.org/en/climatechange/what-is-climate-change#:~:text=Climate%20change%20refers%20to%20long,like%20coal%2C%20oil%20and%20gas."
				target="blank">un.org</a></li>
		<li><a href="https://www.nrdc.org/stories/global-climate-change-what-you-need-know" target="blank">nrdc.org</a></li>
	</ul>
	<h3>Here is a list of charities that help fight this climate crisis:</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><a
				href="https://www.rainforestcoalition.org/donate/#:~:text=Donation%20Options,%2C%20nonprofit%20(501c3)%20organization"
				target="_blank">Coalition for Rainforest Nations</a> is an organization dedicated to creating long-lasting
			solutions for environmental sustainability. As their name implies, they focus on helping save the rainforests from
			changing environments. </li> <img class="rainforest" alt="coalition for rainforest nations"
			src="https://www.rainforestcoalition.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/CfRN_SocialShare_TWITTER_1024x512.jpg"
			alt="Coalition for Rainforest Nations"></img>
		<li><a href="https://www.climateemergencyfund.org/tell-the-truth">Climate Emergency Fund</a> is a fund that helps
			activists be able to peacefully protest and help stop climate change. They get money from donations and then fund
			climate activists who are working to change political policies.</li> <img
			src="https://givingcompass.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/ad9cb30a-4a88-11ec-a3c6-02074da7a271.png"
			alt="Climate Emergency Fund" class="emergencyfund"></img>
	</ul>
	<p>For more information on charities and organizations, visit <a
			href="https://www.tomorrow.io/weather/blog/most-influential-climate-charities-to-donate/"
			target="_blank">tomorrow.io</a>.</p>



